Scope of the Reference Implementation

This release includes:

• structural delivery definitions
• delivery validity rules
• minimal executable reference (message delivery demo)
• outputs and reference traces

STILE defines a deterministic structural model where delivery correctness emerges from structure:

resolve(structure) →

• RESOLVED if structure_aligned
• ABSTAIN if structure is incomplete
• CONFLICT if structure is inconsistent

What This Demonstrates

• delivery correctness without communication
• independence from acknowledgements and retries
• independence from network dependency
• delivery correctness does not require transmission
• structural alignment governing delivery visibility
• safe handling of incomplete or conflicting structure
• deterministic and reproducible delivery states
• identical structure produces identical delivery state and certificate

Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible if it preserves:

• structure-based correctness
• independence from communication as a requirement
• deterministic resolution
• structural alignment-driven visibility
• reproducibility of delivery state and certificate under equivalent inputs
• explicit handling of incomplete and conflicting structure

Conformance is judged solely by observable behavior — not by internal implementation.

S1 = S2 → DeliveryState1 = DeliveryState2 → Certificate1 = Certificate2

Conflict Handling

In this reference implementation:

• CONFLICT is explicitly defined and demonstrated
• ABSTAIN corresponds to incomplete structure (no delivery)
• inconsistent conditions do not influence delivery state

Conformance requires:

• no forced delivery under incomplete structure
• no false confirmation under conflicting structure

Canonical Delivery Identity (Forward Path)

Extended implementations may include canonical identity:

canonical(resolve(S)) → delivery_identity

This enables:

• equivalence across different valid delivery structures
• normalization of delivery truth
• identity independent of representation

This is not required for the reference implementation.

Relationship to Shunyaya Framework

STILE is part of the broader Shunyaya framework.

It builds on:

• SLANG → correctness without execution
• ORL → correctness without ordering
• STINT → correctness without connectivity
• STRAL → correctness without traversal
• STILE → correctness without communication

Each removes a dependency.
Correctness remains preserved by structure.

